==First Aid Kits== [[Image:First aid kit for tropical country - packed.jpg|thumb|The same kit at the left, packed into a single water-tight plastic bag.]] [[Image:First aid kit for tropical country - unpacked.jpg|thumb|left|This first aid kit was packed for a trip to the tropics.]] Everyone should have a well-stocked first aid kit for in the car, at home, and other events. For first aid kits in the workplace, there will be legislation which specifies what must be present; this will depend on the size and type of the workplace and may vary depending on local, regional, or national regulations. Make sure you know where first aid kits are located, whether at home, at work, or at play. First aid kits should be clearly marked; in the workplace, there should be sufficient indication of the kit's location for those who are unfamiliar with its location to identify it.
First aid kits must be kept well-stocked; supplies do expire, and must be replaced periodically. Consider creating a schedule for checking that the kit is stocked, and replacing any expired items as required. Quantities below are guidelines; you should determine what is required based on the kit's expected use.
If possible use a bright-colored, watertight plastic container. Tool boxes are popular, or it may be worthwhile to purchase a kit made specifically for this purpose. {{-}} === Recommended Contents === {|class="wikitable" !Item!!Home!!Car!!Wilderness!!Workplace (<5 workers)<ref name="Good Samaritan Act">[http://www.canlii.org/on/laws/regu/1990r.1101/20071015/whole.html ''First Aid Requirements'', R.R.O. 1990, Reg. 1101] is being used as an example; check the relevant legislation.</ref>!!Workplace (5-15 workers)<ref name="Good Samaritan Act" />!!Workplace (15-200 workers)<ref name="Good Samaritan Act" />||Workplace (>200 workers)<ref name="Good Samaritan Act" /> |- |Nitrile Gloves (pairs)<ref>Using non-latex gloves is important, especially in workplace kits, since you are more likely to be giving treatment to someone who you don't know. Nitrile is always best.</ref>||2||2||10||25<ref name="na">This is not required, but is recommended</ref>||50<ref name="na" />||100<ref name="na" />||200<ref name="na" /> |- |CPR mask||1||1||1||1<ref name="na" />||1<ref name="na" />||1<ref name="na" />||1<ref name="na" /> |- |Tape (roll)<ref>Transpore (3M) is great.</ref>||1||1||2||1||2||4||8 |- |3"x3" sterile gauze pads||4||8||20||4||12||48||96 |- |4"x4" sterile gauze pads||4||8||20||2||2||10||20 |- |Trauma dressing (ABD pad)||0||1||2||2||2||6||10 |- |Non-stick gauze<ref>Look for Telfa; it is the most common variety.</ref>||4||8||20||2<ref name="na" />||2<ref name="na" />||10<ref name="na" />||20<ref name="na" /> |-<!--!Item!!Home!!Car!!Wilderness!!Workplace (<5 workers)!!Workplace (5-15 workers)!!Workplace (15-200 workers)!!Workplace (>200 workers)--> |Roll 2" gauze||1||2||5||2||4||8 |- |Roll 4" gauze||||||||||||8||16 |- |Adhesive bandages||20||40||50||12||24||48||100 |- |Antiseptic solution<ref>Depending on your location, you may not be legally permitted to use this, except with family members. In that case, eliminate it from workplace kits.</ref>||1||1||1||1<ref name="na" />||1<ref 