== Wikiversity, interwiki links ==

Hi Dennis G. Jerz. If I understand your project correctly, you really should be doing this on [[v:Main Page|Wikiversity]], not Wikibooks, since there are going to be both original research aspects and POV aspects (WV was created for this sort of thing). I can import your modules over if you like.

BTW, if you want to link to a Wikipedia article, you just put a "w:" inside the link before the article name, and a "|" after. For example, while <nowiki>[[Bubble gum]]</nowiki> will make a redlink to [[Bubble gum]] on Wikibooks (or Wikiversity), <nowiki>[[w:Bubble gum|]]</nowiki> will create [[w:Bubble gum|Bubble gum]]. --[[User talk:SB_Johnny|<font color="green">'''SB_Johnny'''</font>]] | <sup>[[meta:Wikimedia Pennsylvania|<font color="green">PA!</font>]]</sup> 10:25, 1 December 2007 (UTC)

