* '''[[Fractals/Computer_graphic_techniques/2D#Zoom|zoom]]''' into parameter plane<ref>[http://randomascii.wordpress.com/2011/12/04/really-deep-fractal-zoom-movie-much-faster/ Really Deep Fractal Zoom Movie – Much Faster by Bruce Dawson]</ref><ref>[http://dotat.at/prog/mandelbrot/ Making Mandelbrot Set Movies by Tony Finch]</ref><ref>[http://pauillac.inria.fr/~ddr/mlbrot/ MLbrot by Daniel de Rauglaud]</ref> using automatic determination of Iteration Max number<ref>[http://math.stackexchange.com/questions/16970/a-way-to-determine-the-ideal-number-of-maximum-iterations-for-an-arbitrary-zoom Discussion : A way to determine the ideal number of maximum iterations for an arbitrary zoom level in a Mandelbrot fractal]</ref>
* changing '''coloring scheme''' ( for example color cycling - Fractint)
* changing some parameters of algorithm, for example :
** maximal iteration of escape time algorithm
** bailout value <ref>[http://www.fractalforums.com/general-discussion-b77/dynamic-bailout/ Gif image by jgabase : a wormhole effect on your fractals by changing the bailout dynamicaly]</ref>

